{
  "texts": [
    "Each model is tested using different settings: varied model sizes for FLAN, and distinct temperature parameters in both zero-shot, few-shot, and finetuning approaches for GPT 3.5, LLaMA-1 (through HuggingChat), and LLaMA-2.",
    "We then compare their accuracy, using agreement with trained annotators as a metric, against that of MTurk as well as amongst themselves.",
    "Related workThe practice of fine-tuning transformer models for specialized tasks has become a cornerstone in the field of natural language processing (NLP).",
    "With the advent of large language models (LLMs) like GPT -3.5/4 and Bard (now Gemini), a burgeon- ing body of research is emerging to evaluate their performance and utility across various tasks.LLMs have catalyzed a significant paradigmatic shift in the field of NLP, notably in the area of text annotation.",
    "Their capability to mimic human behavior, understand context, and adapt makes them effective for data annotation tasks [45]."
  ]
}